KATSINA – Katsina State Independent Electoral Commission, KTSIEC, has expressed it’s readiness to conduct the local government elections on Monday 11th April, 2022. Alhaji Ibrahim Bako, the state Chairman of the Commission disclosed this at a press briefing held in Katsina on Tuesday. According to him, with this notice, all stakeholders particularly the political parties should note that, only candidate (s) sponsored by political parties will officially be considered to contest the election. Makinde Condoles With Family of Late Aide, Tijani Wase Greets Senate President, Lawan At 63 He however advised all stakeholders to comply and adhere with the laws and guidelines governing the conduct of local government council in the state. The Commission’s boss added that, the guidelines and timetable for the elections would soon be distributed to all stakeholders to ensure a hitch free elections across the state. Bako also maintained that, all political rallies and campaigns commence from 11th January and ends on 10th April, 2022. While assuring that, the Commission would do it’s best to carry all stakeholders along in all its dealings, he said the Commission would conduct the elections in accordance with the relevant laws.